children.value: A
LngLatBounds

object represents a geographical bounding box,
defined by its southwest and northeast points in longitude and latitude.
If no arguments are provided to the constructor, a
null
bounding box is created.
Note that any Mapbox GL method that accepts a
LngLatBounds

object as an argument or option
can also accept an
Array
of two
LngLatLike

constructs and will perform an implicit conversion.
This flexible type is documented as
LngLatBoundsLike
